// Surfaced 2026-05-22 building the kata-91 bench mirror: an undeclared
// `Type.method` call used to be silently accepted by the typechecker
// (`Type::Error` sentinel), then `parsed.unwrap()` exploded in codegen
// with a misleading "no handler for method 'unwrap' on variable 'parsed'"
// — sending future debuggers chasing a phantom codegen bug. This snapshot
// pins the improved diagnostic: typecheck rejects the call cleanly, and
// `Pipeline::has_fatal_errors` stops the build before codegen runs.
//
// `String.from_utf8` was the original example; once it shipped as a real
// stdlib intrinsic (commit `1b53e8d`), this snapshot migrated to the
// still-unimplemented `String.from_utf16` so the regression guard keeps
// teeth. Any name that resolves to no impl-block method or registered
// `String.*` function would do.
fn main() {
    let buf: Vec[u16] = Vec.new();
    let parsed = String.from_utf16(buf);
    let _ = parsed;
}
